SAPS says its mandate is to ensure people are adhering to lockdown regulations. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The South African Police Service says several arrests have been made, as stop and search operations continue in Sebokeng, West of Johannesburg. SAPS says its mandate is to ensure people are adhering to lockdown regulations. READ: SA lockdown: SANDF, SAPS accused of misconduct Provincial Police Commissioner Elias Mawela is leading a series of stop and search operations. From Saturday afternoon, Commissioner Mawela and MEC Faith Mazibuko have been conducting stop and searches in Sebokeng, West of Johannesburg. READ: The role of SANDF during lockdown People have been arrested for breaking lockdown regulations and transporting banned goods. Police say these impromptu searches will continue.